div1.p: In the District Court, holding Terms at Seattle
In the matter of the application of Jeremiah Mangan for a Writ of Habeas Corpus

This cause coming in to be heard on the writ of habeas corpus heretofore issued herein and the return of John H McGraw thereto, and is appearing from said return that said Jeremiah Mangan is unlawfully retrained of his liberty by said John H McGraw and the it is orderd that said Jeremiah Mangan he and is hereby discharged from custody, and said John H McGraw is hereby ordered to release said Jeremiah Mangan from all restraint, provided however that this only shall not operate to protect nor shall it be a bar to the further prosecution of said Jeremiah Mangan for the same alleged offense for which he was committed by virtue of the commitment referred to in the return of said John H McGraw Said in when Court this 18th day of May A. D. 1889
R- 6867 District Court Application of J. Mangan for writ of H. C Order
